Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a pale red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is very worn, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and remains of at least three lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393969) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393969)
